		{"id":"cmd_reschedule","type":"text","text":"**Calendar time-change event**\nCallSchedulingRequest re-delivered\nMechanism: CALENDAR_INGESTER\n(UC-B1)","x":-2780,"y":-720,"width":400,"height":115,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"cmd_cancel_owner","type":"text","text":"**Cancel by owner**\nPOST /scheduled-calls/cancel-by-owner\nCancelCallService#cancelByOwnerScheduledCall\n(UC-C1)","x":-2780,"y":-340,"width":420,"height":115,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"legend","type":"text","text":"# 🗺️ Event Storming — Cancel & Reschedule (B + C)\n\nUse cases **B1 (Reschedule)** and **C1–C6 (Cancel)**. All paths that deactivate or move a scheduled recording. Cancel state is encoded as `SkipCode + Resolution` — there is no `CallStatus` enum. Every path produces `call-scheduling-updated` with `CRUD = CANCEL` or `UPDATE`.\n\n**Colour key** — 🟧 Event · 🟦 Command · 🟩 Actor · 🟥 Policy · 🟪 Service · ⬛ Data store","x":-3200,"y":-1120,"width":1600,"height":200,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"act_sys_c","type":"text","text":"⚙️ System\n(validation chain / compliance)","x":-3180,"y":340,"width":320,"height":60,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"cmd_cancel_blacklist","type":"text","text":"**Cancel blacklisted**\nPOST /scheduled-calls/cancel-blacklisted\nCancelCallService#cancelBlacklistedCalls\n(UC-C6)","x":-2780,"y":-160,"width":420,"height":115,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"act_ops_c","type":"text","text":"🔧 Ops / compliance\n(via troubleshooter or API)","x":-3180,"y":-132,"width":320,"height":60,"color":"5"},
